payload.text:
Set the website’s typography to use the "Alexandria" Google Font globally across all pages and components.

Requirements:
- Import Alexandria from Google Fonts.
- Apply it as the default font for the entire site (Arabic and English).
- Ensure proper weights (300, 400, 500, 600, 700).
- Configure Tailwind to use Alexandria as the primary font family.
- Confirm the font is applied to headings, body text, buttons, forms, and the course player UI.

Implement:
1) Add to index.html:
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Alexandria:wght@300;400;500;600;700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">

2) Update tailwind.config:
theme: {
  extend: {
    fontFamily: {
      sans: ['Alexandria', 'system-ui', 'sans-serif'],
    },
  },
}

3) Ensure global CSS uses:
body { font-family: Alexandria, system-ui, sans-serif; }

Deliver the updated files and confirm the font is visibly applied site-wide.
